        </persName>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Full length shot of a man in folk costume with military elements, medals, a knife and a pistol in his belt, holding a long rifle. He is seated on artificial rocks, and next to him there is a dog sitting. Painted canvas backdrop, which creates the illusion of the scene being set in nature.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Konstantin (Kosta) Atanasov Panitsa (1857 - 1890) was a Bulgarian volunteer (opaltchenets) in the Serbo-Ottoman War of 1876 and in the Russo-Ottoman war 1877 - 1878, and an Officer. Panitsa was sentenced to death and executed in 1890 because of a charge of conspiracy against Prince Ferdinand I. and Prime Minister St. Stambolov.</ab>
